column4: <content>[paper: geannoteerd; 16pgs.]: The Series of the Months by Pieter Bruegel the Elder. Diane Robbins, Art 498, Winter 1968, Professor F. Grossmann.</content>

<part_of.title>Ad [Addendum] Bruegel: Months. See [Ernst] Buchner, Monats- und Jahreszeitenbilder Hans Wertingers, Zschft f. b.Kst [= Zeitschrift für bildende Kunst], 61, 1927/28, pp. 106-112.</part_of.title>

<parts.title>[vouwblad] Karen Mensel (June 1969), Preference for 24 calendar pictures, sometimes even 36, suggests that the miniaturists (around 1500) were interested in elaborating on the tradition of calendar iconography. A few independent spirits- the more accomplished painters - occasionally break with the more traditional iconography. All calendar pictures, not just the full page illustrations to be taken into consideration. Instances of differing motifs for the same month. [schema: scan: recto-verso];
